  "comments": [
    {
      "text": "This is the flagship class for PHS. If you are taking it, you likely have to take it. It covers a wide range of important methods used in the PHS program and does so in greater depth than first–year statistics but less so than PhD–level biostatistics. Be prepared to spend a decent amount of time completing the assignments because they are long. More importantly, the class helps you bond with other students in your cohort."
    },
    {
      "text": "I had heard this course was a \"trauma bonding\" class –– it's true you bond with your cohort, but I didn't find it to be trauma–inducing at all. It feels like someone is holding your hand through challenging concepts. This is a great course to learn foundational concepts, bond with your cohort, and a great intro to being a PHS PhD student."
    },
    {
      "text": "You can succeed, even if you don't have a strong math background"
    }
  ]
